<h3>Local opens</h3>

<p>Since OCaml 3.12, you can locally open a module within an
expression, using the <code>let open</code> syntax. It can be very
useful when accessing multiple values of a modules, without exposing
them elsewhere:</p>

<code>let open List in
map fst (map (fun x -&gt; (x,1)) [1;2;3;4])</code>


